HEADWORD: Ademption
<hw>A*demp"tion</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*d⟦ecr⟧mp"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>ademptio</ets>, fr. <ets>adimere</ets>,
<ets>ademptum</ets>, to take away; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>emere</ets> to
buy, orig. to take.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The revocation or
taking away of a grant, donation, legacy, or the like.</def>
